# 💰 Malek's Home Budget PWA — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Build a **bilingual (EN/AR) Progressive Web App** for personal/family budget management. The app replaces the current Google Sheets workflow with a modern, mobile-first experience while maintaining the ability to import existing Sheet data. Both Malek and his wife (آية) share the same household data in real-time.

**Currency**: Jordanian Dinar (JD)
**Users**: Malek + آية (shared household)
**Hosting**: Firebase Hosting (free)

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Firebase Project Setup**: You will need to create a free Firebase project. I will guide you through this step-by-step during execution. It requires a Google account (which you already have).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Google Sheets "Parallel" Use**: The app will have an **Import from Google Sheets** feature. You can continue using Sheets if you want, and import that data into the app at any time. However, the app will NOT auto-sync with Sheets in real-time — you'd manually trigger an import. Over time, the app's built-in transaction entry should be easier than using Sheets directly.

> [!WARNING]
> **Push Notifications**: Push notifications require Firebase Cloud Messaging setup and HTTPS. They will work on Android but have limited support on iOS Safari (iOS 16.4+). Visual in-app alerts will always work on all platforms.

