## Data Model (Firestore)

### Collections Structure

```
households/
  {householdId}/
    name: "Malek & Aya's Budget"
    members: ["malek@gmail.com", "aya@gmail.com"]
    currency: "JD"
    createdAt: timestamp

users/
  {uid}/
    email: string
    displayName: string
    householdId: string
    language: "en" | "ar"
    createdAt: timestamp

months/
  {householdId}_{YYYY_MM}/          # e.g., "abc123_2026_01"
    householdId: string
    year: 2026
    month: 1                         # 1-12
    expenseCategories: [
      { name: "بنزين", nameEn: "Fuel", planned: 100 },
      { name: "اكل برا", nameEn: "Eating Out", planned: 20 },
      ...
    ]
    incomeCategories: [
      { name: "الراتب", nameEn: "Salary", planned: 1295 },
      { name: "Cash", nameEn: "Cash", planned: 0 },
      ...
    ]
    createdAt: timestamp
    createdBy: uid

transactions/
  {autoId}/
    householdId: string
    monthKey: "2026_01"              # for easy querying
    date: timestamp                   # actual transaction date
    amount: number                    # always positive
    type: "expense" | "income"
    category: "بنزين"                # Arabic category name (matches month config)
    description: "بنزين ٢٠ لتر"
    createdBy: uid                    # who entered it
    createdAt: timestamp
    updatedAt: timestamp
```

### Key Design Decisions
- **Household concept**: Both users belong to one household. All data is shared at the household level.
- **Month document**: Stores the planned budget per category for that specific month. Categories can vary month-to-month.
- **Transactions**: Flat collection with `householdId` and `monthKey` for efficient querying.
- **Category names in Arabic**: Since your categories are in Arabic, we store the Arabic name as the primary key and optionally an English translation for the bilingual UI.

